    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Before we start editing files, lets get familiar with some basic movements.</p>\n<p>Navigate back to the empty directory and type in the following.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token function\">vim</span> test.js</code></pre></div>\n<p>You are now in <code class=\"language-text\">NORMAL</code> mode.  This probably doesn't feel all that normal.\nAnd you are right, its really not that normal.</p>\n<h2 id=\"lets-talk-modes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lets-talk-modes\" aria-label=\"lets talk modes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lets talk Modes</h2>\n<p>There are a few modes that you should be aware of.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Normal</li>\n<li>Insert</li>\n<li>Visual</li>\n<li>Visual Line</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"my-first-if-statement\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#my-first-if-statement\" aria-label=\"my first if statement permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>My First If Statement</h2>\n<p>Lets write our first if statement.</p>\n<p>Currently, you are in <code class=\"language-text\">NORMAL</code> mode.  This is where you can execute commands\nto navigate, edit, and execute vim/sys commands.  To get out of this mode,\npress <code class=\"language-text\">i</code></p>\n<p>After pressing <code class=\"language-text\">i</code> you should see something like <code class=\"language-text\">-- INSERT --</code> in the bottom\nleft hand side of vim.</p>\n<p>Now that you are in insert mode, type the following</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Press <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;esc></code> or <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Ctrl-c></code> (abbreviated <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;C-c></code>) to leave <code class=\"language-text\">INSERT</code> mode and back\nto <code class=\"language-text\">NORMAL</code>.</p>\n<p>Goodness, isn't default vim ugly?</p>\n<p>type <code class=\"language-text\">:q</code> to quit vim.  Also, don't tell anyone.</p>\n<h2 id=\"my-first-moves\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#my-first-moves\" aria-label=\"my first moves permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>My First Moves</h2>\n<h3 id=\"basic-navigation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#basic-navigation\" aria-label=\"basic navigation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basic navigation</h3>\n<p>time to curl down our first little exercise</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ThePrimeagen/vim-fundamentals/master/course-website/lessons/exercise-0-hjkl-x.md <span class=\"token operator\">></span> exercise.md <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token function\">vim</span> exercise.md</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"deleting-yanking-and-pasting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#deleting-yanking-and-pasting\" aria-label=\"deleting yanking and pasting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Deleting, Yanking, and Pasting</h3>\n<p>These are going to be some of your fundamental movements within vim.  This is\nwhere you will see some significant speed ups compared to a conventional editor.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ThePrimeagen/vim-fundamentals/master/course-website/lessons/exercise-1-dyp.md <span class=\"token operator\">></span> exercise.md <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token function\">vim</span> exercise.md</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"insert\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#insert\" aria-label=\"insert permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Insert!</h3>\n<p>We are going to go over entering into insert mode</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ThePrimeagen/vim-fundamentals/master/course-website/lessons/exercise-2-insert.md <span class=\"token operator\">></span> exercise.md <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token function\">vim</span> exercise.md</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"recap\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#recap\" aria-label=\"recap permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Recap</h2>\n<p>Lets talk about what happened.  I would love to get some feedback from you.\nWhat do you think about all of this nonsense?  Does it seem like to much?  Or\ndoes it seem exciting?  I hope you are excited.</p>\n<h3 id=\"we-learned\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#we-learned\" aria-label=\"we learned permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>We learned</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>h,j,k,l for basic movement.</li>\n<li>w,b for word hopping.  Effectively the same as Option/Ctrl + arrow keys</li>\n<li>yy to \"copy\" a line, called Yank</li>\n<li>dd to delete, and yank, a line</li>\n<li>p and P to paste the contents of the implicit register below / above</li>\n<li>Most of the ways to go into insert mode!\n<ul>\n<li>i and a for which side of the cursor</li>\n<li>I and A for which side of the line</li>\n<li>o and O for belowe / above line</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>zz - I snuck that one in...</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That is a grand total of 16 different motions</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/basic-usage","title":"Using Vim","order":"5A","section":"Basics","description":"Let's use vim for the first time!"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"fron